The paper discusses the problem of adversarial examples in neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG and cs.CV). The paper also proposes a method for hiding these adversarial examples from network interpretation, which involves techniques from cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper uses deep learning models, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural engineering (cs.NE).
